---
import Layout from "@/layouts/main.astro"
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { BookOpenIcon, ArrowLeftIcon } from "lucide-react"
---

<Layout title="React Deep Dive | Never Stop Learning">
  <div class="flex min-h-svh flex-col">
    <header class="border-b px-6 py-4">
      <nav class="mx-auto flex max-w-3xl items-center justify-between">
        <a href="/never-stop-learning" class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <BookOpenIcon class="size-6" />
          <span class="text-lg font-semibold">Never Stop Learning</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/never-stop-learning/courses" class="text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground">All Courses</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main class="flex-1 px-6 py-12">
      <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
        <a href="/never-stop-learning/courses" class="mb-6 inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground">
          <ArrowLeftIcon class="size-4" /> Back to courses
        </a>

        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">React Deep Dive</h1>
        <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">12 lessons &middot; Intermediate</p>

        <div class="mt-8 space-y-8">
          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Overview</h2>
            <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
              Go beyond the basics of React. This course explores hooks in depth, state management strategies, rendering performance, and battle-tested patterns used in production applications.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Lessons</h2>
            <ol class="mt-3 list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-muted-foreground">
              <li>Component Patterns and Composition</li>
              <li>Hooks: useState, useEffect, and Beyond</li>
              <li>Custom Hooks and Logic Reuse</li>
              <li>Context API and State Management</li>
              <li>Performance: Memoization and Lazy Loading</li>
              <li>Server Components and Streaming</li>
              <li>Forms and Validation</li>
              <li>Testing React Components</li>
              <li>Routing and Navigation</li>
              <li>Data Fetching and Caching</li>
              <li>Error Boundaries and Resilience</li>
              <li>Deploying React Applications</li>
            </ol>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Prerequisites</h2>
            <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
              Familiarity with JavaScript and basic React concepts (components, props, JSX).
            </p>
          </section>

          <div class="rounded-lg border bg-muted/50 p-6 text-center">
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">This is demo content. The full course is coming soon.</p>
            <Button client:load className="mt-4" variant="outline">Stay Tuned</Button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </main>

    <footer class="border-t px-6 py-6 text-center text-sm text-muted-foreground">
      Never Stop Learning &copy; {new Date().getFullYear()}
    </footer>
  </div>
</Layout>
